.DT
sayto
Discworld player help
sayto

.SH Name
.SI 5
sayto - Direct a say to someone in the room.
.EI

.SH Syntax
.SI 5
sayto <person> [#lang] [@adverb] <text>
sayto <person> [#'lang'] [@adverb] <text>
.EI

.SH Description
.SP 5 5
Sayto sends the message to all the people in the room and also makes the
message look directed.  With a normal say you would see:

Furball says: hello

With sayto you would see:

Furball says to Pinkfish: hello

The # and @ can be used to use a specific language and an adverb to the
message.  You can use partial matching for a language, so for example
#dj will make you speak in djelian.  You may also put the language name
in quotes after the # to speak in languages which have spaces in them.
.EP

.SH Examples
.SI 5
> sayto pinkfish hello
> sayto drem The sun shines out of your eyes and drowns me in sweet surprise.
> sayto gototh Whooo!  Look at that coffee table!  The inlay!
> say sojan #djelian @happily This is in djelian.
> say sojan #dj @happily This is in djelian.
> say sojan #'djelian' @happily This is in djelian.
.EI

.SH See also
.SI 5
say, emote, lsay, shout, tell, whisper.
.EI
